paragraph.content:
with the prior written consent of the Director, granting extensions of the
                validity periods of the Certificates referred to in paragraph (b) that are issued by
                the organization;

cause a non-Hong Kong ship that is within the waters of Hong Kong to be
                    surveyed under Part II as if the ship were a Hong Kong ship;
                    and

within the period commencing 3 months before and ending 3 months after the
                    second anniversary date of the Certificate issued in respect of the ship;
                    or

the Director has reasonable grounds to believe that important repairs or
                    renewals have been made to the ship after an IOPP Certificate or a HKOPP
                    Certificate has been issued in respect of the ship;

the Certificate is not endorsed under regulation 5, or under
                Regulation 6 of Annex I, after an annual survey of the ship is carried
                out;

the Certificate is not endorsed under regulation 6, or under
                Regulation 6 of Annex I, after an intermediate survey of the ship is carried out;
