subsection.def:
oil fuel capacity (燃油容量), in
                relation to an oil fuel tank, means the volume of a tank in m3, at 98%
                filling;

subparagraph.content:
the Director is satisfied that the ship is fitted with a holding tank
                        having a volume adequate for the total retention on board of the oily bilge
                        water;

the Director is satisfied that adequate reception facilities are
                        available to receive such oily bilge water at the place of
                        discharge;

